## 14. Customer Notification and Document Request Framework

### 14.1 Overview

As part of the Enhanced Due Diligence workflow, the system must support a **Customer Notification Framework** that enables communication with customers when additional KYC information or documentation is required.

The framework must allow:

- Generation of customer notifications
- Request for additional KYC documentation
- Centralized message governance
- Multi-channel notification delivery

This framework must operate as part of the **EDD Case Management workflow** within the **FLOW system**.

### 14.2 Trigger Conditions

Customer notifications may be triggered when:

1. A customer is classified as **High Risk**
2. Additional documentation is required for **EDD review**
3. Data inconsistency is detected between T24 and QCB API
4. Regulatory requirements require additional verification

Triggers may originate from:

| Source | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| T24 Customer Data | Missing or outdated KYC information |
| Re-KYC System | Periodic review requirements |
| QCB KYC API | Regulatory compliance gaps |
| AML Indicators | Transaction-based alerts |
| KYC Data Inconsistency | Mismatch between internal and external data |

### 14.3 QCB Data Integration

The system must support integration with **Qatar Central Bank KYC APIs**.

When a customer is classified as **High Risk**, the system must attempt to retrieve additional information from QCB systems including:

- Regulatory KYC information
- Identification data
- Regulatory flags
- Compliance indicators

**Integration Rules:**

| Condition | System Behavior |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Data successfully retrieved | Present to employee within EDD case view |
| No data returned from QCB API | Continue using internal KYC data |
| API timeout or error | Log error, proceed with internal data, notify IT support |

### 14.4 Customer Notification Creation

When additional documentation is required, the system must allow **Business users** to create a notification request.

**Process Flow:**

```
┌─────────────────┐
│ Business Maker  │
│ (Create Request)│
└────────┬────────┘
         ↓
┌─────────────────┐
│Business Checker │
│ (Verify & Approve)│
└────────┬────────┘
         ↓
┌─────────────────┐
│Marketing Approval│
│ (Content Review) │
└────────┬────────┘
         ↓
┌─────────────────┐
│  Customer       │
│  Notification   │
└─────────────────┘
```

The message content must be created by the **Business team** using structured templates approved by Marketing.

### 14.5 Message Governance

All customer notification messages must be approved by the **Marketing Department**.

**Approval Workflow:**

| Stage | Role | Action |
|-------|------|--------|
| 1 | Business Maker | Create notification request |
| 2 | Business Checker | Verify case details and approve |
| 3 | Marketing Maker | Review message content |
| 4 | Marketing Checker | Final approval |
| 5 | System | Notification sent to customer |

Once approved, the message becomes part of the **official notification library** for future reuse.

### 14.6 Notification Template Library

The system must maintain a **centralized message template library** containing commonly used messages.

**Standard Message Templates:**

#### Salary Verification Request
```
Dear Customer,

As part of our ongoing KYC review, please provide a copy of your salary certificate.

Reference Number: [CASE ID]
Required Document: Salary Certificate
Deadline: [SLA DATE]

Thank you for your cooperation.
Qatar Islamic Bank
```

