## 45. Organizational Hierarchy Data Integrity

### 45.1 Overview

The system shall enforce strict **data integrity rules** for organizational hierarchy records to prevent duplicate entries, inconsistent titles, and invalid reporting lines.

This section ensures that UI groupings, pilot labels, and display sections do not create invalid organizational nodes in the system database.

---

### 45.2 Single Record Principle

The system shall enforce a **single official organizational record** for each employee:

| Rule | Enforcement |
|------|-------------|
| **No Duplicate Nodes** | Each employee appears only once per manager |
| **Single Reporting Line** | One active reporting line per employee (unless matrix governance) |
| **Single Official Title** | One approved title per organizational context |
| **Single Department Assignment** | One primary department assignment |

**Validation Query:**

```sql
-- Check for duplicate employee records under same manager
SELECT employee_id, manager_id, COUNT(*) as duplicate_count
FROM org_hierarchy
GROUP BY employee_id, manager_id
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
```

---

### 45.3 Display Grouping vs Organizational Hierarchy

The system shall clearly distinguish between:

| Type | Purpose | Creates Org Node? |
|------|---------|-------------------|
| **Organizational Hierarchy** | Official reporting structure | ✅ Yes |
| **Display Grouping** | UI visual organization | ❌ No |
| **Department Section** | Logical grouping for navigation | ❌ No |
| **Pilot Label** | Temporary identification | ❌ No |

**Display Grouping Rules:**

Any display section such as "Department Managers" shall be treated as a **visual grouping only** and shall NOT create:
- A separate reporting line
- An ownership node
- An approval hierarchy entry
- A duplicate employee record

